# HTML Structure Guidelines - Liquid Glass Snowcap Portfolio

## Semantic Structure
- Use semantic HTML5 elements throughout
- Proper heading hierarchy (h1, h2, h3)
- Semantic sections: `<header>`, `<main>`, `<section>`, `<footer>`
- Accessible navigation with `<nav>`

## Page Structure
```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <!-- Meta tags, title, CSS -->
</head>
<body>
  <header>
    <nav>
      <!-- Projects, Contact links -->
    </nav>
  </header>
  
  <main>
    <section id="hero">
      <!-- Hero content with mountain background -->
    </section>
    
    <section id="projects">
      <!-- Project tiles -->
    </section>
    
    <section id="ridge">
      <!-- Ridge reveal with glass panels -->
    </section>
  </main>
  
  <footer>
    <!-- Contact information -->
  </footer>
</body>
</html>
```

## Accessibility Requirements
- Proper `lang` attribute
- Semantic landmarks and ARIA labels
- Alt text for decorative SVGs
- Focus management
- Keyboard navigation support

## SVG Mountain Implementation
- Inline SVG for the snowcapped mountain
- Layered semi-transparent panels
- Proper viewBox and responsive scaling
- Accessible with `aria-hidden="true"` if decorative

## Content Guidelines
- Hero H1: "Scaling ideas into reliable systems"
- Subtext: "I build AI/ML-powered web systems with clean UX and measurable outcomes."
- Ridge tagline: "Reliable. Measurable. Elegant."
